title: For Sale:  TAURUS PRO TITANIUM .380 ACP ULTRA LITE REVOLVER!!!
postcontent:
This is a Taurus Pro Titanium M.380 ACP Ultra Lite revolver (5-shot). Again, it shoots .380 ACP and NOT 38 SPECIALS. This is a very rare revolver, as I am unaware of any other revolver on the market today that shoots the .380 caliber. It's an incredible handgun and shoots flawlessly. It is also extremely light, very thin/streamlined, and the perfect gun for anyone wanting to wear a revolver and keep it concealed easily.  I actually bought this gun new for my wife back in February but she wants to sell it to buy a subcompact semi auto.  I took the gun to the range for the first time last weekend and only put 10 rounds through it.  I loved the gun so much I want it for myself but as I already have 3 other handguns I carry, rifles, a tactical shotgun, etc. she wants me to sell it.  The ONLY reason she wants to sell it is because after I shot that 10th round through the gun, a cease fire was called at the range.  A range officer came by and I asked him about CHL classes at their location and he noticed the revolver.  He reminded me that if you qualify for your CHL license with a revolver, then you are only licensed to carry a revolver.  You have to qualify with a semi-auto to be able to carry any handgun.  Once I told my wife, she decided she wanted a semi-auto of her own.  

I just HATE selling this gun as it is so rare and I believe will only go up in value.  In addition, I just love the size (easily concealable), the weight (Ultralight Titanium), the accuracy (even though the barrel is only 1.75") and the recoil is not nearly as bad as I expected since the gun weighs so little.  I have the original box and all original paperwork and manuals that came with the gun new.  Again, it's only had 10 shots fired since I bought it new and I cleaned it thoroughly before and after my trip to the range. So basically you are getting a NEW gun.

The price is $399.99 for the handgun itself, all original manuals/paperwork, the original box, the special key that activates/deactivates the "Taurus Security System" (see below for additional details on this system). and FIVE brand new auto loaders that work fantastic with this gun!!!  The first person to contact me and pay the $399.99 will get all of the above.  See note below regarding shipping of this firearm.

This revolver has numerous, fantastic features that I have not seen in other revolvers or at least they don't seem to work as well in other revolvers.  A few of these features are:

1) Adjustable hammer tension - this is great for those who are not used to the trigger pull on a double action firearm.  It also allows the gun owner to adjust this to his/her preference.
2) Adjustable Trigger Stop - the trigger stop can be adjusted in or out to the owner's preference.
3) Adjustable Front and rear sights - sights can be adjusted "permanently" to sight the gun in or adjusted for windage or both.  A very easy turn of the screw with a small screw drivers is all that is required.
4) The "Taurus Security System" - this handgun is equipped with the exclusive Taurus Security System.  The system is designed to preclude the use of the revolver when the mechanism is engaged.  It consists of an integral mechanism located on the back of the hammer.  When properly engaged by the use of the included key, it prevents the firing of the revolver completely.  The engagement of the mechanism can only be done utilizing the special (and included) key that fits the activation pin.  Engaging and disengaging this system is extremely easy and simply requires the insertion of the key into the activation pin and a turn clockwise to engage it (Secure) and a counterclockwise turn to disengage it (Ready to Fire).  This is a fantastic security feature and replaces the need for a trigger guard for safety.  However, I do have a trigger guard for this handgun and will also include it with the sale, if requested.
5) The Taurus Titanium revolvers are designed to withstand the regular use of +P jacketed ammunition.

NOTE ON DELIVERY OF THIS HANDGUN:

Local buyers - all buyers within 30 miles of my home, I will gladly agree to meet halfway.  Local buyers that live over 30 miles away are welcome to drive to a mutually agreed upon place (no further than 15 miles from my home) and we can handle the sale there.  In addition, I can ship to buyers in Texas not wanting to make the drive.

NON-LOCAL buyers - I have a very reliable FFL licensed location from which I can ship your handgun.  

SHIPPING/HANDLING CHARGES - the person I use to ship all handguns only charges $10 plus actual shipping expenses.  Most FFL dealers charge between $20-30 for this service.  All handguns are shipping on Tuesday - Thursdays only and the buyer is responsible for all shipping and handling charges.  I will do my best to ensure that the shipping, handling (and insurance charges) are minimized for you.  In addition, postal insurance on the package for the full value of the firearm is required.

Thanks for viewing my ad and let me know if you are interested or have any further questions!

 The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

  The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

THIS SATURDAY IN BARDSTOWN!

Regular Price: $50

The class lasts about 7 hours total, includes a written and range test, basic handgun safety, handgun cleaning, handgun knowledge, handgun marksmanship, and qualifies you to apply for a CCDW license in KY. Students should bring a modern functioning handgun with 50 rounds of factory new ammunition and appropriate cleaning supplies for the firearm. Don’t have a handgun, ammo, or supplies? No worries! Get in touch with me and we can work out the details. There is also a $60 fee divided between the state and local police that is normally paid 2-3 weeks after the completion of the course. A criminal background check will be done by the Kentucky State Police after the completion of the course. Due to high volume, it is currently taking up to 5 months after the class for the actual license to be issued by the Kentucky State Police.
